# ERP Workspace Tabs Standard

**Status:** IMPLEMENTED (UI.4A through UI.4G complete)
**Last updated:** ERP GLOBAL UI.4G

---

## Rule 1 — Workspace is the only navigation model after 4A

After ERP GLOBAL UI.4A is implemented, all sidebar navigation must use the workspace tab system.

```ts
// CORRECT — after 4A
workspaceStore.openTab({ route: "/admin/master-data/parties", title: "All Parties", icon: "Building2", tabKind: "list" })

// FORBIDDEN after 4A — do not hard-navigate via Link in sidebar
<Link href="/admin/master-data/parties">All Parties</Link>
```

Exception: External links (URLs outside the app) may still use `<a target="_blank">`.

---

## Rule 2 — Every route must be registered in the workspace route registry

All protected routes must have a corresponding entry in:

```
src/lib/workspace/workspace-route-registry.ts
```

Each entry defines:
- `route`: exact path or pattern
- `title`: human-readable tab title (string or function)
- `icon`: Lucide icon name string
- `tabKind`: `"list"` | `"record"` | `"dashboard"` | `"settings"` | `"utility"`
- `singleton`: `true` for list/utility routes (re-click switches, doesn't open duplicate)
- `closable`: `false` for dashboard only

```ts
// CORRECT — registry entry
{ route: "/admin/master-data/parties", title: "All Parties", icon: "Building2", tabKind: "list", singleton: true }

// FORBIDDEN — opening a tab without a registry entry
workspaceStore.openTab({ route: "/some/unregistered/route", title: "???" })
```

---

## Rule 3 — Tab naming conventions

| Tab kind | Format | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Dashboard | "Dashboard" | Dashboard |
| List page | Module name | All Parties |
| Typed list | Type name | Customers |
| New record | "New {Entity}" | New Party |
| Edit/View record | "{Entity} — {Name or Code}" | Party — ABC Contracting |
| Settings | "Settings" | Settings |

Do not use long IDs or database keys as tab titles. Use human-readable names.

---

## Rule 4 — Singleton tabs: switch don't duplicate

List and utility routes are singleton (`singleton: true`). If already open, clicking the sidebar item switches to the existing tab without creating a duplicate.

```ts
// Implementation in openTab:
const existing = tabs.find(t => t.route === route)
if (existing) {
  setActiveTab(existing.id)
  router.push(route)
  return
}
```

---

## Rule 5 — Record tabs allow multiple instances

Record tabs (`tabKind: "record"`) may have multiple instances open simultaneously if they represent different entity IDs. Clicking "Edit" on two different Party records opens two separate tabs.

```
Party — ABC Contracting [id: 1]
Party — XYZ Holdings [id: 2]
```

Clicking "Edit" on a record that is already open switches to the existing record tab.

---

## Rule 6 — Maximum open tabs

```ts
const MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS = 8  // initial
const HARD_MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS = 10
```

If max reached, show toast:
```
"Maximum tabs open. Close a tab before opening a new one."
```

Do not silently close an existing tab to make room.

---

## Rule 7 — Dashboard tab is pinned and non-closable

```ts
{ route: "/dashboard", tabKind: "dashboard", closable: false, pinned: true }
```

The Dashboard tab cannot be closed. It is always the leftmost tab.

---

## Rule 8 — Tab dirty indicator

When a form inside a workspace tab has unsaved changes:

1. The form must call `workspaceStore.markDirty(tabId, true)`
2. The tab chip shows an amber pulse dot
3. The tab close button remains active but triggers `UnsavedChangesDialog` before close

```tsx
// Bridge in useRecordWorkspaceForm:
useEffect(() => {
  workspaceStore.markDirty(tabId, isDirty)
}, [tabId, isDirty])
```

Never close a dirty tab silently.

---

## Rule 9 — Closing a dirty tab requires confirmation

```tsx
// On tab close button click:
if (tab.dirty) {
  showUnsavedChangesDialog({
    onDiscard: () => { workspaceStore.markDirty(tabId, false); workspaceStore.closeTab(tabId) },
    onStay: () => { /* do nothing */ }
  })
} else {
  workspaceStore.closeTab(tabId)
}
```

---

## Rule 10 — Browser close/navigate away warning

If any open tab has `dirty: true`, register `window.onbeforeunload` to warn the user.

```ts
// In WorkspaceProvider:
useEffect(() => {
  const hasDirty = tabs.some(t => t.dirty)
  window.onbeforeunload = hasDirty ? (e) => { e.returnValue = ""; return ""; } : null
  return () => { window.onbeforeunload = null }
}, [tabs])
```

---

## Rule 11 — Tab persistence in localStorage

After every tab open/close/switch, persist tab metadata to localStorage.

```ts
// Key
const STORAGE_KEY = "erp_workspace_tabs"
const ACTIVE_KEY = "erp_workspace_activeTabId"

// What to persist — metadata only
type PersistedTab = Pick<WorkspaceTab, "id" | "route" | "title" | "subtitle" | "icon" | "tabKind" | "closable" | "pinned">
```

**NEVER store in localStorage:**
- Form field values
- Passwords, tokens, session data
- Sensitive business data (bank accounts, IDs)
- `dirty` state (always reset to false on restore)

On restore, revalidate each tab's route against current user permissions. Drop unauthorized tabs silently.

---

## Rule 12 — Child dialogs BLOCK the full workspace (UI.4G)

**Design decision (UI.4G):** Child forms are intentional BLOCKING modal tasks.

When a child dialog (`ERPChildDialogForm`) is open:

1. The full-screen overlay (z-[100]) covers the workspace including the tab bar and sidebar.
2. Workspace tab switching is blocked — the tab bar (z-[30]) is behind the overlay.
3. Outside click and Esc are blocked — the user MUST cancel or save explicitly.
4. Only the child dialog content (z-[110]) and combobox dropdowns (z-[120]) are interactive.
5. The owning record form content must be inert + opacity-50 (via `isChildDialogOpen`).

**DO NOT raise the tab bar above z-[30] or lower the child dialog overlay below z-[100].**
This would break the blocking behavior and allow tab switching while a child form is open.

---

## Rule 13 — Sidebar coming-soon items stay disabled

Items marked `comingSoon: true` in `navGroups` must remain as disabled `<div>` elements. Do not connect them to `openTab`. Do not create stub routes.

---

## Rule 14 — Direct URL and browser refresh

On `WorkspaceProvider` mount:
1. Read `location.pathname`
2. Restore tabs from localStorage
3. If pathname matches a restored tab, activate it
4. If pathname does not match any restored tab, create a new tab for it using the registry
5. Navigate to the active tab's route

---

## Rule 15 — ERPDrawerForm remains allowed for small quick-setup forms

Forms with fewer than 5 fields and no child tables may continue using `ERPDrawerForm`.

```
ALLOWED to keep ERPDrawerForm:
- Geography (Countries, Emirates, Cities, Areas, Ports)
- Finance Basics (Currencies, Payment Terms, Tax Types, Banks, Cost/Profit Centers)
- UOM (Categories, Units, Conversions)
- Lookups (Categories, Values)
- Organizations, Branches, Roles, Numbering Rules

MUST migrate to ERPRecordWorkspaceForm (see erp-record-workspace-form-standard.mdc):
- Party Master
- Customers (after Party Master)
- Future: Employee, Fleet Asset, Purchase Order, Job Card
```

---

## Rule 16 — No custom tab widths or colors per module

All workspace tabs use the global tab chip style. Do not add per-module custom backgrounds, gradients, or font sizes to tabs.

Active tab: `bg-background border-b-2 border-primary text-foreground`
Inactive tab: `bg-muted/50 text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground hover:bg-muted`
Dirty indicator: `h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-amber-500 animate-pulse`
Close button: `h-4 w-4 text-muted-foreground hover:text-destructive`

