## Rule 17 — All list/table screens must cache UI state (UI.4E)

Every implemented and future workspace list/table screen must preserve safe UI state when the user switches workspace tabs and returns.

**For screens using ERPDataTable:** automatic — no additional code needed.
The `tableId` prop must be unique per route/screen. `ERPDataTable` persists:
- search text (`globalFilter`)
- page index and page size
- sorting state
- column visibility, sizing

**For screens with custom state outside ERPDataTable:** use `useWorkspaceTableState`:

```ts
import { useWorkspaceTableState } from "@/hooks/use-workspace-table-state";

const { search, setSearch, pagination, setPagination } = useWorkspaceTableState({
  key: "my-table",
  scope: "route",
  identifier: "/admin/my-module",
});
```

**Sensitive data:** Never persist passwords, tokens, PII, bank account numbers, IBAN, or unsaved form field values in localStorage. See `docs/standards/ERP_GLOBAL_WORKSPACE_OPEN_ELEMENT_CACHE_STANDARD.md`.

---

## Rule 18 — Record forms must cache active section and scroll state (UI.4E)

All `ERPRecordWorkspaceForm` usages must wire `useWorkspaceSectionState`:

```ts
import { useWorkspaceSectionState } from "@/hooks/use-workspace-section-state";

const [activeSection, setActiveSection] = useWorkspaceSectionState(
  party?.id
    ? { key: "active-section", initialSection: "basic", scope: "record", recordType: "party", recordId: party.id }
    : { key: "active-section", initialSection: "basic", scope: "tab", identifier: activeTab?.id }
);
```

Scroll state via `useWorkspaceScrollState` and the `bodyScrollRef` prop of `ERPRecordWorkspaceForm` is strongly recommended for new record form implementations.

---

## Rule 19 — Z-index standard for overlays (UI.4G)

| Layer | Z-index | Notes |
|-------|---------|-------|
| App/page content | base | |
| Workspace tab bar | `z-[30]` | Intentionally below child dialog overlay |
| Drawer / Sheet | `z-[50]` | |
| Child dialog overlay | `z-[100]` | Full-screen; blocks tab bar and sidebar |
| Child dialog content | `z-[110]` | |
| ERPCombobox / Popover inside child dialog | `z-[120]` | |
| Alert / confirm dialog | `z-[130]` | |
| Toast | top layer | |

**Critical constraints:**
- Tab bar MUST stay at `z-[30]` — raising it would allow tab switching while child form is open.
- Child dialog overlay MUST be `z-[100]` — lowering it would not block the tab bar.
- ERPCombobox MUST be `z-[120]` — ensures dropdown appears above dialog content (z-[110]).

ERPCombobox applies `z-[120]` globally — no per-form hacks needed.
